      "content": "The main argument for regulating AI to prevent existential risks is that the tech industry's lack of accountability and oversight has led to an unregulated proliferation of advanced AI systems that could potentially outsmart and surpass human intelligence, posing an existential threat to humanity. This is particularly concerning given the rapid advancements in AI capabilities, which have been largely unregulated and unaccountable to human values. By regulating AI, we can ensure that its development aligns with human values and minimizes the risk of catastrophic consequences.",
